news.title: HC reserves order on Ansals plea to suspend seven-year jail term in Uphaar case
news.para: ​Justice Subramonium Prasad heard the arguments on behalf of counsel for Ansals, another convicted person Anoop Singh Karayat, Delhi Police, and Association of the Victims of Uphaar Tragedy (AVUT).

news.title: Macrotech has managed to pull off deleveraging as well as a growth story: Abhishek Lodha
news.para: “Ours is a deleveraging cum growth story which is not easy to pull off but we find that we are able to deliver on both fronts. Our cost of debt has moderated by 120 bps or 1.2% over the last nine months and we expect this to significantly fall going forward.”

news.title: India initiates anti-dumping probe against imports of vinyl tiles from China, Taiwan, Vietnam
news.para: Welspun India Ltd, Welspun Flooring Ltd and Welspun Global Brands Ltd had filed a petition before the directorate to impose anti-dumping duty on the imports from China, Taiwan and Vietnam, according to a notification of the DGTR.

news.title: Two Greater Noida housing societies penalized over waste management
news.para: The action was taken on instructions of GNIDA CEO Narendra Bhooshan against Galaxy North Avenue and Victory One Amayra societies in Greater Noida (West) which have been slapped with Rs 40,400 and Rs 10,200 penalties, respectively, it said.

news.title: ED arrests Karvy stock broking CMD & CFO in money laundering case
news.para: ​The agency produced the two-- already lodged in central jail, Bengaluru after being arrested by the police-- before a special Prevention of Money Laundering Act (PMLA) court in Hyderabad on January 20 and on January 25 it remanded them to four days of ED custody from January 27-30, it said in a statement.

news.title: China property shares slump as planned U.S. rate hike adds to woes
news.para: Regulatory curbs on borrowing have driven China's property sector into crisis, highlighted by Evergrande, the world's most indebted property firm. The contagion has engulfed other Chinese developers, roiled global financial markets in the past year and contributed to a slump in China's property market, which accounts for a quarter of its economy.

news.title: China Resources and two other state builders secure funding for acquisitions
news.para: C&D Real Estate Corp Ltd and China Merchants Shekou Industrial Zone Holdings Co said in separate statements that they raised 1 billion yuan, and 1.29 billion yuan, respectively, through bond sales to fund purchases of real estate projects.

news.title: China's Xiamen city to require developers to place all deposits in escrow
news.para: Authorities will make sure that the funds placed in the escrow accounts are used first for the purchase of construction materials and equipment and the payment of construction costs and taxes, the Xiamen government said in rules published on its website on Monday.

news.title: Budget 2022 expectations from the real estate sector
news.para: In order to meet the Government’s vision of Housing for All, investments in affordable housing and rental housing should be further encouraged.

news.title: UK landlords raise rents for new tenants by record 9.9%: Survey
news.para: Average residential rents for homes advertised on property website Rightmove during the three months to December 2021 were 9.9% higher than in the same quarter a year earlier, the biggest rise since the data series began in 2011.

news.title: Tamil Nadu to unveil mega sports city on East Coast Road; 500 acres identified
news.para: A 500-acre Rs 700-crore mega sports city is set to take shape on the city outskirts, with such swanky facilities like finest athletic tracks, indoor cycling velodrome, hockey stadium, multipurpose indoor stadium for basketball, volleyball and boxing.

news.title: China Evergrande targets restructuring proposal within six months as state tightens control
news.para: Once China's top developer, Evergrande has racked up debts of more than $300 billion and is struggling to repay creditors, suppliers and investors in wealth management products.

news.title: Bengaluru civic body to issue notices to property tax defaulters
news.para: BBMP chief commissioner Gaurav Gupta, who tested positive for Covid, held a virtual meeting to discuss property tax collection on Wednesday.

news.title: ESR acquires around eight acres of land in Delhi from TARC
news.para: The Indian warehousing segment has attracted large institutional investors, allocating fresh capital to the warehousing segment as demand continues to be strong from e-commerce and logistic firms and easing of policies, including the GST reform.

news.title: Noida: 416 housing plots up for grabs near Jewar airport site
news.para: The plots range from 120-500 sqm and 1,000-4,000 sqm, while the asking circle rate is between Rs 17,400 and Rs 17,800 a sqm.
